bigipAgentStart.desc: An indication that the agent has started running.

bigipAgentShutdown.desc: An indication that the agent is in the process of being shut down.

bigipAgentRestart.desc: An indication that the agent has been restarted.(eg. It happens when a SIGHUP is received.)This does not imply anything about whether the configuration haschanged (unlike the standard coldStart or warmStart traps)

bigipCpuFanSpeedLow.desc: CPU fan speed is too low.

bigipCpuFanSpeedBad.desc: CPU fan speed signal not received.

bigipChassisPowerSupplyBad.desc: Chassis power supply status is bad.

bigipStandby.desc: The system is going into standby mode.

bigipActive.desc: The system is going into active mode.

bigipActiveActive.desc: The system is going into active-active mode.

bigipFeatureFailed.desc: A high availability feature triggered action failed.

bigipFeatureOnline.desc: A high availability feature is now responding.

bigipTamdAlert.desc: Too many authentication failures (> 60) in 1 second toTMM (Traffic Management Module).

bigipAggrReaperStateChange.desc: The aggressive reaper state changed. Aggressive reaperstate changes indicate the system is moving into distress-modefor DOS prevention.

bigipNetLinkDown.desc: An internal interface link is down. This is for L1 and L2.These are internal links within the box connecting the CPUand Switch subsystems, which should never lose link.If they do, it indicates a serious problem.

bigipDiskPartitionWarn.desc: The disk partition free space is very limited, which isless than a specified limit. By default, the limit is setto 30% of total disk space.

bigipDiskPartitionGrowth.desc: The disk partition exceeds the specified growth limit.By default, the limit is set to 5% of the total disk space.The growth is difference of two consecutive monitoring data.

bigipLogEmerg.desc: The system is in an unusable situation.

bigipLogAlert.desc: Action must be taken immediately for the system to workproperly.

bigipLogCrit.desc: The system is in a critical condition.

bigipLogErr.desc: The system has some error conditions.

bigipLogWarning.desc: The system is experiencing some warning conditions.

bigipCompLimitExceeded.desc: The compression license limit is exceeded.

bigipSslLimitExceeded.desc: The SSL license limits are exceeded,either for TPS (Transactions Per Second) orfor MPS (Megabits Per Second).

bigipExternalLinkChange.desc: An external interface link status changes.For a fixed port, this is an occurrence when network cablesare connected or removed, and the network is reconfigured;for a pluggable port (such as a SFP or XFP port), this happenswhen the pluggable unit is plugged in or unplugged,or when a cable is connected or removed from a plugged port.The possible values are UP, DOWN, DISABLED, or UNPOPULATED.

bigipAsmRequestBlocked.desc: The HTTP request was blocked because it issued (at least one)violation(s) which is marked as blocking at the current activepolicy in Application Security Module.

bigipAsmRequestViolation.desc: The HTTP request issued a violation to the current active policy.This violation is marked as an alerting violation in that policyin Application Security Module.

bigipGtmPoolNotAvail.desc: A pool is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolDisabled.desc: A pool is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolEnabled.desc: A pool is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmLinkNotAvail.desc: A link is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmLinkDisabled.desc: A link is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmLinkEnabled.desc: A link is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmWideIpNotAvail.desc: A wide IP is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmWideIpDisabled.desc: A wide IP is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmWideIpEnabled.desc: A wide IP is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolMbrAvail.desc: A pool member is becoming available in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolMbrNotAvail.desc: A pool member is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolMbrDisabled.desc: A pool member is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmPoolMbrEnabled.desc: A pool member is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmServerNotAvail.desc: A server is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmServerDisabled.desc: A server is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmServerEnabled.desc: A server is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmVsNotAvail.desc: A virtual server is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmVsDisabled.desc: A virtual server is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmVsEnabled.desc: A virtual server is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmDcAvail.desc: A data center is becoming available in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmDcNotAvail.desc: A data center is becoming unavailable in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmDcDisabled.desc: A data center is disabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmDcEnabled.desc: A data center is enabled in global traffic management module.

bigipGtmAppObjAvail.desc: An application object is becoming available in global management module.

bigipGtmAppObjNotAvail.desc: An application object is becoming unavailable in global management module.

bigipGtmAppAvail.desc: An application is becoming available in global management module.

bigipGtmAppNotAvail.desc: An application is becoming unavailable in global management module.

bigipStandByFail.desc: In failover condition, this standby will not be able to go active.

bigipGtmBoxAvail.desc: The box is becoming available in global management module.

bigipGtmBoxNotAvail.desc: The box is becoming unavailable in global management module.

bigipAsmFtpRequestBlocked.desc: The FTP request was blocked because it issued (at least one)violation(s) which is marked as blocking at the current activepolicy in Application Security Module.

bigipAsmFtpRequestViolation.desc: The FTP request issued a violation to the current activepolicy. This violation is marked as an alerting violationin that policy in Application Security Module.

bigipGtmBig3dSslCertExpired.desc: BIG-IP GTM BIG3D SSL Cert has expired.

bigipGtmBig3dSslCertWillExpire.desc: BIG-IP GTM BIG3D SSL Cert will expire.

bigipGtmSslCertExpired.desc: BIG-IP GTM SSL Cert has expired.

bigipGtmSslCertWillExpire.desc: BIG-IP GTM SSL Cert will expire.

bigipAsmSmtpRequestViolation.desc: The FTP request issued a violation to the current activepolicy. This violation is marked as an alerting violationin that policy in Application Security Module.

bigipBladeNoPower.desc: A blade lost power. The blade may be pulled out

bigipClusterdNoResponse.desc: The cluster daemon failed to respond for 10 or more seconds.

bigipAsmDosAttackDetected.desc: DoS attack detected by Application Security Module.

bigipAsmBruteForceAttackDetected.desc: Brute force attack detected by Application Security Module.
